Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_metric_definition(25.10)                      get_metric_definition(25.10)

Name
       get_metric_definition  - Returns the metric definition of the specified
       metric

Syntax
       get_metric_definition

       -help

       [-id <metric_id>]

       -name <metric_name>

       Returns the metric definition of the specified metric.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each get_metric_definition parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man get_metric_definition

       -id <metric_id>
              Specifies the database ID to output.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -name <label_name>
              Specifies the metric name.

              Data_type: string, required

Examples
              * The  following  command  queries  the  attributes  of the tim-
                ing.setup.wns metric:

                innovus 1> get_metric_definition -name timing.setup.wns

                metric timing.setup.wns

                units ns

                type slack

                description {Worst negative setup slack (all path groups)}

                dp 3

                cmp moreBetterBelowTarget

                target 0

              *

                The following command queries all defined metrics:

                innovus 1> foreach m [get_metric_definition -name *] {puts  $m
                }

